<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Thompson</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October 11,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Gresham instructs Mr. Thompson to exert himself in favor of the innocent
                        trade of American vessels and of the legitimate inward and outward trade of
                        merchandise belonging to the citizens of the United States.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>